nihs_available:
nihs_disease: Available on NIHS
Value set: True/False
gbd_column:
nihs_column: name of the cause_name that corresponds to this term
Value set: free text
disease:
Disease: The disease that the rates reflect
Value set: free text
demographic_cat: Demographic category: Either Race or gender. Value set: binary
source_title: title of publication or report
source_year:
Year(s): Year or range of years that rates were collected (not year of publication)
Value set: Year in YYYY, or year range in YYYY-YYYY
source_loe:
Source Level of Evidence: The level of evidence of the source material (see “guidelines for deciding which disease rates sources to use” below)
Value set:
1: Government or international agency (e.g., WHO) reporting
2: Peer-reviewed publication that is reporting non-government collected data
3: Other
4: None
source_loe_notes:
Describe “Other” source level. Leave blank for government reporting and peer-reviewed publication, 
Value set: free text
source_url:
Source: The source of the data for rates. Please copy and paste a link to the source
Value set: url
data_type:
Prevalence or incidence: Whether the rates are prevalence or incidence rates
Value set:
1: Prevalence (n per 10,000)
2: Incidence (n per 10,000 person-years)
data_type_notes: describe other. for example if only relative prevalences are available compared to true raw figures per normalised unit
disease_value_1:
If demographic category:
- Gender= Male 
- Race= White
disease_value_2:
If demographic category:
- Gender= Female 
- Race= Black/African American
disease_value_3:
If demographic category:
- Gender= Non-binary 
- Race= Hispanic/Latino
disease_value_4:
If demographic category:
- Gender= NA 
- Race= Asian
disease_value_5:
If demographic category:
- Gender= NA 
- Race= Indiginous
disease_value_6:
If demographic category:
- Gender= NA 
- Race= Pacific Islander
notes: Provide any notes on the data here
researcher_1:
The person doing the manual searching and completion of the text
Value set: 
Jaya
Arvind
Ajay
researcher_2:
The person doing the verification of the figures using the source_url provided
Value set: 
Danielle
Jack
verified:
Verified: If the figures have been verified for use
Value set: Binary 1/0
